-- A BRIEF PROLOGUE --
> 🌙 Nighttime, a few days before formal mission debrief.
🌃 Ready to put a close on the day's work, you all finally exit the office after being held hostage for an extra few minutes: you had to be given your next undertaking. No rest for the weary indeed. It was oddly bare--a case of unspecified "anomalous disturbances," and a poster who promised to follow up with more information in the next couple of days. One might wonder how an assignment like this even got approved, but there was nothing you could do about it except wait until the agreed upon time.
You see a few men talking across the street. A rather mundane observation for a detective such as yourself, but with the spike in violent assaults as of late, one can never be too cautious. It's too far away to make out what they're saying. But perhaps under the dull moonlight, you can glimpse what they're doing? If you're nosy, that is.
